- internal_bulb: Internal Indicator Lamp [inside enclosure: cube_load] [NOTE: This lamp is connected in parallel with the main load and reflects voltage conditions across that branch.]
- load_diode: Load Protection Diode [inside enclosure: cube_load]
- load_cable_pos: Load Input Cable (+)
- load_cable_neg: Load Input Cable (−)

Instruction: With the control module confirmed to deliver only ~0.36 V at its output when the lamp is expected ON, open the load module. Using the control module output (≈0.36 V on +, 0 V on −), measure: (1) voltage directly at the load module input terminals; (2) voltage on the anode and cathode of the series diode that precedes the lamps; (3) continuity (ohms, with power off) from the load module − input terminal to the lamp return node. Confirm whether any unexpected series element, mis‑wiring, or internal short in the load module is loading the control module output and clamping it near 0.36 V.
