Instruction: With power on and the relay commanded ON, measure the voltage at three points all with respect to the PSU negative: (1) the 12 V feed on the PCB just before it enters the relay contact; (2) the relay contact output pad on the PCB (the node that then goes to the “Control Output Cable (+)” terminal); and (3) the voltage directly on the Control Output Cable (+) terminal itself. Compare these three readings to see where the ~12 V is dropping to ~0.36 V, which will distinguish a high‑resistance PCB trace / connector / terminal fault between the relay contact and the output cable from an internal load or sensor‑circuit loading that pulls down the node.
